It’s understood the demonstrators have damaged a section of the Gautrain station and traffic lights. JOHANNESBURG - Violent protests have broken out at Riverlae by people from the Zama Impilo informal settlement. It’s understood the demonstrators have damaged a section of the Rea Vaya station and traffic lights. Law enforcement officials are on the scene. Metro police spokesperson Superintendent Wayne Minnaar: “Motorists are advised to avoid Commando Road between Main Reef and Albertina Sisulu Road. Officers are on the scene diverting traffic.” The demonstrations come a day after protests broke out near Eldorado Park and Nasrec. 